The father of a teenager who drowned in the River Avon paid tribute yesterday to his ‘chip off the old block’.

Jay Burgess said 14-year-old Aaron was ‘always acting the fool’, adding that his son was ‘beautiful’.

Aaron was one of two teenagers who drowned on Tuesday while cooling off during the mini-heatwave in the south of the country.

