The second boy to die on Tuesday was 
15-year-old Daniel James McCullagh, who had been swimming in the River 
Nene near his home in Woodford, Northamptonshire. It is believed Daniel 
had been jumping into the water with friends moments before the tragedy 
at 3pm.

His friends tried to save him when his
body slipped under the water, but he was swept away by the strong 
current. Rescue crews found his body just over three hours later, almost
half a mile away from where he disappeared.

Daniel’s father Gabriel last night described him as a ‘lovely, funny lad who just wanted to fit in and have loads of friends’.

